<TITLE> Chittagong forest chief, deputy suspended </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 28 (bdnews24.com)Two forest officials, allegedly on the run, of Chittagong division, have been suspended, a senior official said Thursday. Mokhlesur Rahman, Chittagong divisional commissioner, told bdnews24.com that conservator of forests Atiqul Azam and his deputy Tapan Kumar Dey were put under suspension as they faced corruption charges and also because they were absconding. Earlier on June 24, the joint forces searched the foresters' offices and homes. Neither of the officers was present in his office or home. On June 25, the joint forces raided Tapan Kumar Dey's office at Sholoshahar and seized Tk 18 lakh in cash and some documents. bdnews24.co
